          These Terms & Conditions (“Terms”) are a legal agreement between you
          and <strong>{COMPANY_NAME}</strong> (“FennaAI”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) governing
          your use of the FennaAI software, websites, and services (collectively,
          the “Service”).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>2. Your Privacy & Local Processing</h2>
        <p>
          FennaAI is designed to run <strong>locally on your device</strong>.
          Your files and training data remain on your machine by default. We do
          not access your content, your models, or your conversations unless you
          explicitly share them with us for support.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>3. Accounts & Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be capable of forming a binding contract to use the Service.
          If you create an account, you agree to provide accurate information
          and keep it up to date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>4. Your Content & Ownership</h2>
        <p>
          You own the content you use to teach or interact with your AI, as well
          as the <strong>locally produced artifacts</strong> (e.g., tuned model weights
          saved on your device) subject to any applicable third-party model or dataset
          licenses. You are responsible for ensuring you have the rights to use the
          content you provide.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>5. Open-Source Models & Third-Party Components</h2>
        <p>
          FennaAI enables you to download and run open-source models and tools
          that may be licensed under their own terms. Those third-party terms
          govern your use of those components. Where there is a conflict,
          third-party licenses control for those components.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>6. Permitted & Prohibited Use</h2>
        <p>
          You may use FennaAI for personal or business purposes in compliance
          with applicable laws. You may not use the Service to create or
          distribute illegal content; violate privacy or intellectual property
          rights; interfere with or disrupt the Service; or attempt to
          reverse-engineer parts of the software except where permitted by law
          or by an open-source license.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>7. Credits & Payments</h2>
        <p>
          Credits, when offered, are used <strong
            >only for training/fine-tuning</strong
          > models within FennaAI. Chatting and file Q&A features are free and do
          not consume credits. Payments are processed by third-party providers; their
          terms and privacy statements apply to payment details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>8. Updates & Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may provide updates to improve performance, security,
          compatibility, and features. The Service may change over time. Where
          materially impactful, we will make reasonable efforts to notify users
          via the app or website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-animate-on-scroll>
        <h2>9. Beta & Experimental Features</h2>
        <p>
          Some features may be labeled beta or experimental and may be less
          stable than other parts of the Service. You use these features at your
